## **Model Building**

* **Backbone:** MobileNetV2 (pretrained on ImageNet, offline weights).
* **Classifier head:**

  * GlobalAveragePooling2D
  * Dense layer (128 units, ReLU)
  * Dense output (1 unit, sigmoid for binary classification)

```python
import tensorflow as tf

base_model = tf.keras.applications.MobileNetV2(
    input_shape=(160,160,3),
    include_top=False,
    weights="/kaggle/input/datasets/me221522/mobilnet/mobilenet_v2_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels_1.0_160_no_top.h5"
)
base_model.trainable = False

inputs = tf.keras.Input(shape=(160,160,3))
x = tf.keras.applications.mobilenet_v2.preprocess_input(inputs)
x = base_model(x, training=False)
x = tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D()(x)
x = tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation="relu")(x)
outputs = tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation="sigmoid")(x)

model = tf.keras.Model(inputs, outputs)
model.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(1e-3),
              loss="binary_crossentropy",
              metrics=["accuracy"])
```

